      "author": "godfatherlg",
      "description": "## v1.6.7 - Fix url.parse deprecation warning\r\n\r\n### Fixed\r\n- Replaced Node.js `path` module with Obsidian-compatible path functions to resolve `url.parse()` deprecation warning\r\n- Removed dependency on deprecated `url.parse()` method that was causing warnings in Node.js environments\r\n- Implemented custom path handling functions ([dirname](file://c:\\Users\\Administrator\\OneDrive\\桌面\\fakelink\\main.ts#L46-L49), [basename](file://c:\\Users\\Administrator\\OneDrive\\桌面\\fakelink\\main.ts#L51-L54), [relative](file://c:\\Users\\Administrator\\OneDrive\\桌面\\fakelink\\main.ts#L56-L80)) that work within Obsidian's ecosystem\r\n\r\n### Changed\r\n- Updated internal path resolution logic to be fully compatible with Obsidian's file system\r\n- Maintained all existing functionality while eliminating external Node.js dependencies\r\n\r\nThis update addresses the deprecation warning that was appearing during plugin submission to Obsidian's official repository.",
